   custom `DataRef` class that ensures dereferencing is only done on valid,
   managed data. This prevents accidental null dereferences by enforcing
   initialization and ownership semantics. For example:
   
   ```cpp
   struct DataRef {
       std::unique_ptr<int> data;
   
       int& get() { if (!data) throw std::runtime_error("Null data"); return *data; }
   };
   
   struct Bob {
       DataRef* data;
   };
   ```
   
   This design ensures that any access to `data` is validated and avoids raw
   pointer chains entirely, preventing null pointer errors at runtime and
   enforcing the invariant that `data` is always valid.
